Recruitment specialist Glassdoor has published a new guide on the most common interview questions prospective employees can expect to face in 2020. The list is based on tens of thousands of interview reviews to find out some of the most common interview questions candidates get asked during recent interviews, the group said. “When it comes to the interview process, research, and preparation for the interview can oftentimes determine your chances of making it to the next step. “One of the best ways to get ready for a virtual job interview is to practice your responses to the most common interview questions.” The top 50 most common questions are outlined below, based on how frequently they appear. Read: Michael Jordaan on what’s next for companies post Covid-19